attacks.phishing.phishing_page module

attacks.phishing.phishing_page.attack_view(request)[source]

View function for rendering the attack page.

Renders the phishing attack page, providing necessary context data such as the base URL for making attacks and the available phishing choices.

Parameters: - request: HTTP request object.

Returns: - HTTP response rendering the attack page.

attacks.phishing.phishing_page.phishing_page_view(request, url)[source]

View function for rendering a phishing page.

Retrieves the phishing object corresponding to the provided URL, extracts the template name, and renders the page.

If a query parameter ‘q’ is provided, attempts to create an incident for the specified target and phishing attack.

Parameters: - request: HTTP request object. - url: URL of the phishing page.

Returns: - HTTP response rendering the phishing page.

attacks.phishing.views module

attacks.phishing.views.incident_callback(request)[source]

Callback function for recording incidents.

Receives incident data via POST request, logs the incident, and returns a success response.

Parameters: - request: HTTP request object.

Returns: - JsonResponse: Response indicating the status of the incident recording.

attacks.phishing.views.webhook_receiver(request)[source]

Receiver function for processing webhook alerts.

Receives alert data via POST request, processes the alerts, logs the data, and returns a success response.

Parameters: - request: HTTP request object.

Returns: - JsonResponse: Response indicating the status of the alert processing.
